@startuml
!include ../../style.puml

title Little's Law: System Queuing Model

actor "Clients" as clients
box "Disk" #LightCyan
  queue "Queue" as queue
  database "Storage" as disk
end box

' [step1 {"name":"Arrival Rate (λ)"}]
clients -> queue: Write Requests\nArrival Rate (λ)
note right of clients: iostat: r/s + w/s
' [/step1]

' [step2 {"name":"Queue Time (Wq)"}]
note over queue: Requests wait in line\nQueue Time (Wq)
' [/step2]

' [step3 {"name":"Service Time (S)"}]
queue -> disk: Dequeue & Write Data
note over queue, disk: Service Time (S)\ne.g., 0.5ms/write\n(iostat: svctm)
' [/step3]

' [step4 {"name":"Throughput & Total Time"}]
disk --> clients: Write Complete & Ack\nThroughput (X)
note over clients, disk: Total Response Time (W) = Wq + S\n(iostat: await)
' [/step4]

' [step5 {"name":"Little's Law Formula"}]
note over clients, disk #E6F3FF
  **Little's Law mapping to iostat**
  **L = λ x W**
  avgqu-sz (Total in System) = (r/s + w/s) x await
end note
' [/step5]

@enduml
